@chapter Introduction
@section Introduction
@cindex Introduction

Triton is a standard Amiga shared runtime library.  Triton makes it much
easier to create good looking graphical user interfaces (GUIs) than
GadTools, BOOPSI or other systems.

The most important features are:

@itemize @bullet
@item
Object oriented system
@item
Automatically font sensitive, font adaptive
@item
Automatic keyboard shortcuts for default window actions
@item
@emph{Really} easy to use
@item
Beautiful customizable AmigaOS3.x look
@item
Comes as a freely distributable shared library
@item
Size! It's the Triton among the minnows of GUI creation systems ;)
@item
Easy installation: For a quick installation simply put triton.library
into @file{Libs:} or the current directory.
@item
Resizability of windows wherever applicable
@item
A Preferences editor which allows you to customize the look and feel of all
Triton GUIs
@item
No installation required. Simply putting triton.library into the current
directory is enough for a minimum installation.
@end itemize

By using Triton you don't have to worry about otherwise very time-consuming
things like font-sensitivity and resizability of your windows.  What is
even more important is that you can easily change your user interfaces
later without having to rearrange display objects.  Simply add an object to
a group and the whole GUI will adapt to make room for it.

